(a)  A petition invoking the jurisdiction of the court under this part shall be entitled "In the matter of the protection of ____________________," and shall be verified.
	(b)  The petition shall set forth with specificity the:



	(1)	Reasons the person is considered to be a dependent adult;
	(2)	Facts which bring the dependent adult within this part;
	(3)	Name, birth date, sex, and residence address of the dependent adult;
	(4)	Names and addresses of any living persons, or entities required to be notified pursuant to section 346-237; and
	(5)	If appropriate, allegations describing any lack of capacity of the dependent adult. [L 1989, c 381, pt of §1; am L 1990, c 144, §1 and c 234, §9]
